"""Intent 02 buying_by_voices — Pattern A LangGraph for voice-driven cart
operations per D-S08-NN-A LAW (Voice Session Memory Hybrid cornerstone) +
D-S08-NN-B LAW (Voice Action Intent Enum) + D-S08-NN-01..11 LAW chain.

S-08 T01.B (Phiên Sx08-D) — Backend Services Layer.

Graph topology (per docs/04_INTENT_SPECS.md Intent 02 post-T01.I reconcile):

    START
      ├─► load_voice_context
      │     - Redis GET voice:context:{user_id} → state.voice_history
      │       (separate key from RedisSaver checkpoint per D-S08-NN-A
      │       cornerstone; TTL 30min refresh-on-read=True, FIFO 5 turns)
      │     - cart.get MCP → state._cart_data (S-05 D-S05-02 LAW reuse)
      │     - emit status SSE phase='load_context'
      │
      ├─► speech_transcribe
      │     - speech.transcribe MCP (Gemini 2.5 Flash audio per D-S08-NN-03)
      │     - populate state.voice_text + state.voice_confidence
      │     - emit voice_transcribed SSE (NEW T01.G per D-S08-NN-02 LAW)
      │     - emit partial_text SSE for cosmetic typewriter feel
      │       (D-S08-NN-07 LAW — no real STT partial)
      │     - on E_TRANSCRIBE_FAILED / E_NO_SPEECH:
      │         emit error SSE + route to final terminal
      │
      ├─► parse_voice_intent
      │     - LLMClient.generate_json (15s timeout, D-S08-NN-04 LAW)
      │     - prompt = parse_voice_intent.txt (5-shot VN, voice_history +
      │       cart_snapshot context injection per D-S08-NN-A)
      │     - populate state.voice_action + state.voice_parsed_items
      │     - emit understanding SSE with ai_summary_vi
      │     - on LLMTimeout / malformed JSON:
      │         emit error SSE E_INTENT_PARSE_FAILED + route to final
      │
      ├─► [conditional edge: _route_by_voice_action]
      │       ├─► action=='add' OR 'update_qty' → resolve_items
      │       │     - asyncio.gather(*[vespa.hybrid_search per item])
      │       │       (D-S08-NN-05 LAW parallel)
      │       │     - populate state.voice_matched_products
      │       │     - apply MATCH_THRESHOLD_HIGH=0.85 / LOW=0.6 (env-tunable
      │       │       per D-S08-NN-10 LAW)
      │       │     ↓
      │       │     [conditional edge: _route_after_resolution]
      │       │       ├─► all matched (≥0.85) → bulk_cart_commit
      │       │       ├─► some ambiguous (0.6..0.85) →
      │       │       │     emit status awaiting_user_input
      │       │       │     interrupt({awaiting:'clarify_pick'})
      │       │       │     (Pattern A — D-S08-NN-01 LAW; resume on FE
      │       │       │      sendAction('clarify_pick', {product_id}))
      │       │       └─► all no_match (<0.6) →
      │       │             voice_no_match_alts (S-05 D-S05-04 LAW reuse)
      │       │
      │       ├─► action=='remove' → voice_cart_remove
      │       │     - resolve product_id from state._cart_data by voice match
      │       │     - cart.update_qty(qty=0) MCP (auto-removes per cart.py
      │       │       L476 sugar path)
      │       │     - emit cart_updated SSE
      │       │     → save_voice_context
      │       │
      │       └─► action=='query' → voice_recall
      │             - recall from voice_history (NO Vespa, NO cart mutation)
      │             - emit partial_text SSE with ai_summary_vi from LLM
      │             → save_voice_context (DOES update history with query turn)
      │
      ├─► bulk_cart_commit (action=add|update_qty path)
      │     - Redis pipeline loop cart.update_qty per item (D-S08-NN-08 LAW)
      │     - emit cart_updated SSE (D-S08-NN-02 reuse)
      │     → co_purchase_lookup
      │
      ├─► co_purchase_lookup (S-04 D-S04-NN reuse per D-S08-NN-05 LAW)
      │     - analytics.co_purchased fixture lookup (or stub for S-08 fallback)
      │     - emit co_purchase_hint SSE if match found
      │     → save_voice_context
      │
      ├─► save_voice_context
      │     - Redis SET voice:context:{user_id} JSON with FIFO truncate 5 turns
      │     - TTL 30min refresh-on-read=True per D-S08-NN-A LAW
      │     - this turn includes {request_id, user_utterance, action,
      │       parsed_items, matched_products, ai_summary_vi, ts}
      │     → final
      │
      └─► final node
            - emit final SSE event
            - await saver.adelete_thread(rid) — Strategy β fast-path cleanup
              per D-S04-13 LAW (same pattern as searching_by_text.py +
              cart_by_text.py). voice:context PERSISTS in separate Redis
              key — D-S08-NN-A cornerstone (cleanup of RedisSaver checkpoint
              does NOT touch voice:context).

Reuses (100% per handoff Sx08-C §2.3 reuse-max breakdown):
    - state.IcpState — extended +8 voice fields per T01.E (state.py amendment)
    - tools.llm_client.get_llm_client + LLMTimeout — 15s timeout default
    - tools.mcp_client.McpClient + McpError — JSON-RPC 2.0 client (speech.
      transcribe, vespa.hybrid_search, cart.get, cart.update_qty,
      analytics.co_purchased)
    - tools.redis_publisher.RedisPublisher.publish_sse — all SSE events
      including NEW voice_transcribed (T01.G shared-types extension)
    - prompts.load_prompt — for parse_voice_intent.txt +
      voice_no_match_reason.txt
    - langgraph.checkpoint.redis.aio.AsyncRedisSaver — caller-owned lifecycle
      per Phiên Sx04-7 fix LAW (compile_*_graph(saver, publisher) signature)
    - redis.asyncio — for voice:context:{user_id} ops (separate from saver)

4 voice error codes per D-S08-NN-11 LAW (JSDoc-only in error.dto.ts, S-07
E_VISION_BLUR precedent):
    - E_TRANSCRIBE_FAILED   — speech.transcribe timeout / Gemini error
    - E_INTENT_PARSE_FAILED — LLM parse empty / malformed JSON
    - E_PERMISSION_DENIED   — FE-side (NOT raised here, documented for
                              FE-BE contract completeness)
    - E_NO_SPEECH           — audio too small / empty transcription

Reference:
    - slices/S-08_decisions-log.md D-S08-NN-A LAW cornerstone +
      D-S08-NN-B LAW + D-S08-NN-01..11 LAW (13 D entries Section 1)
    - slices/S-08_decisions-log.md C-S08-A..N (14 C entries Section 2,
      ALL resolved via 13 D-NN LAW; mid-task Phiên Sx08-D surfaces:
      C-S08-O = ai.client.ts + action-poster.ts manual sync;
      C-S08-P = main.py 2 dispatch blocks Block 1 + Block 2 patch)
    - docs/handoff/00/PHASE_00_INTENT_02_MOCKUP_HANDOFF.md §3-4 (MAR-1 Q1-Q4)
    - Mockup intent-02-state-A-listening.html ... state-G-error.html
    - apps/ai/src/graphs/intents/searching_by_text.py Pattern A precedent
      (L900-974 canonical compile_*_graph + L735-815 _node_co_purchase_lookup)
    - apps/ai/src/graphs/intents/cart_by_text.py interrupt-resume mechanics
      (L185-200 + L524-542) + Strategy β cleanup L626-655
"""

from __future__ import annotations

import asyncio
import json
import os
import time
from typing import Any, Optional

import redis.asyncio as aioredis
import structlog
from langgraph.checkpoint.redis.aio import AsyncRedisSaver
from langgraph.graph import END, START, StateGraph
from langgraph.types import Command, interrupt
from opentelemetry import trace

from ...state import IcpState
from ...tools.llm_client import LLMTimeout, get_llm_client
from ...tools.mcp_client import McpClient, McpError
from ...tools.redis_publisher import RedisPublisher
from ...prompts import load_prompt

_tracer = trace.get_tracer(__name__)
_logger = structlog.get_logger()

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Constants — env-tunable per D-S08-NN-10 LAW; default values verified Phiên
# Sx08-A MAR-1 Q4 LOCKED + Phiên Sx08-C source-audit.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

VOICE_CONTEXT_TTL_S = 30 * 60  # 30 minutes per D-S08-NN-A LAW
VOICE_CONTEXT_MAX_TURNS = 5  # FIFO truncate per D-S08-NN-A LAW
MAX_VOICE_ITEMS = 10  # R-S08-6 soft cap per parse_voice_intent.txt instruction 3
LLM_PARSE_TIMEOUT_S = 15.0  # D-S08-NN-04 LAW (mirrors S-04 default)
SPEECH_MCP_TIMEOUT_S = 30.0  # MCP HTTP outer timeout; speech.py inner 15s default

# Match thresholds per D-S08-NN-10 LAW (env-tunable for prod tuning).
MATCH_THRESHOLD_HIGH = float(os.getenv("ICP_VOICE_MATCH_HIGH", "0.85"))
MATCH_THRESHOLD_LOW = float(os.getenv("ICP_VOICE_MATCH_LOW", "0.6"))

# C-S08-Q (Phiên Sx08-D2): Vespa hybrid_search scores live on a 0..~30
# absolute scale, so the 0..1 HIGH/LOW thresholds above never discriminate
# (a junk query top1 ~7 looks identical to a valid ambiguous top1 ~7).
# Discrimination signal is SEPARATION between top1 and top2, not absolute
# value. Per D-S08-NN-10 LAW (env-tunable):
#   - top1 < MIN_SCORE                  -> treat item as no_match
#   - top2/top1 >= RATIO_AMBIGUOUS      -> ambiguous (clarify chip-row)
#   - else                              -> confident match (commit)
VOICE_MIN_SCORE = float(os.getenv("ICP_VOICE_MIN_SCORE", "4.0"))
VOICE_RATIO_AMBIGUOUS = float(os.getenv("ICP_VOICE_RATIO_AMBIGUOUS", "0.90"))


def _voice_match_class(m: dict) -> str:
    """Classify a resolved voice item: "match" | "ambiguous" | "no_match".

    Ordinal picks (match_score == 1.0 sentinel, single candidate) are
    always confident. Otherwise use top1 absolute floor + top2/top1 ratio.
    """
    top1 = float(m.get("match_score") or 0.0)
    cands = m.get("candidates") or []
    # Ordinal reference path sets match_score=1.0 with a single candidate;
    # treat as confident (no Vespa scale involved).
    if m.get("resolution") == "ordinal":
        return "match"
    if m.get("matched_product") is None or top1 < VOICE_MIN_SCORE:
        return "no_match"
    top2 = 0.0
    if len(cands) >= 2:
        top2 = float((cands[1] or {}).get("match_score") or 0.0)
    if top1 > 0.0 and (top2 / top1) >= VOICE_RATIO_AMBIGUOUS:
        return "ambiguous"
    return "match"


def _voice_candidate_chip(c: dict) -> dict:
    """C-S08-R: shape one Vespa candidate hit for FE state-D chip-row.

    Mockup intent-02-state-D-clarify.html .opt-chip needs: name/title,
    price, rating, sold_count, stock, plus thumb (image_icon/gradient).
    All fields are read verbatim from the Vespa hybrid_search hit (live
    probe Phiên Sx08-D3 confirmed every key present). match_score kept for
    FE debug/sort; score key dropped (Vespa never returns it).
    """
    c = c or {}
    return {
        "id": c.get("id") or c.get("product_id"),
        "title": c.get("title") or c.get("name"),
        "price": c.get("price"),
        "original_price": c.get("original_price"),
        "rating": c.get("rating"),
        "rating_count": c.get("rating_count"),
        "sold_count": c.get("sold_count"),
        "stock": c.get("stock"),
        "brand": c.get("brand"),
        "image_url": c.get("image_url"),
        "image_icon": c.get("image_icon"),
        "image_gradient": c.get("image_gradient"),
        "match_score": c.get("match_score"),
    }

# Vespa per-query result cap for resolve_items (we only need top candidates
# for threshold logic + clarify chips).
VESPA_RESOLVE_LIMIT = 10

# Voice action enum per D-S08-NN-B LAW.
_VOICE_ACTIONS_MUTATE = {"add", "update_qty", "remove"}
_VOICE_ACTIONS_ALL = {"add", "update_qty", "remove", "query"}


def _mcp_url() -> str:
    return os.getenv("MCP_URL", "http://mcp:5050/rpc")


def _redis_url() -> str:
    return os.getenv("REDIS_URL", "redis://redis:6379/0")


def _voice_context_key(user_id: str) -> str:
    return f"voice:context:{user_id}"


def _now_iso() -> str:
    return time.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ", time.gmtime())


# ============================================================================
# Voice context Redis helpers (D-S08-NN-A LAW cornerstone)
# ============================================================================


async def _load_voice_context_redis(user_id: str) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:
    """Load voice:context:{user_id} from Redis. Returns [] if missing.

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW: separate Redis key from RedisSaver checkpoint
    (intent:checkpoint:{rid}). TTL 30min refresh-on-read=True. Shape:
    {turns: [{request_id, user_utterance, action, parsed_items,
              matched_products, ai_summary_vi, ts}, ...]} FIFO 5.
    """
    client = aioredis.from_url(_redis_url(), decode_responses=True)
    try:
        raw = await client.get(_voice_context_key(user_id))
        if not raw:
            return []
        # Refresh TTL on read per D-S08-NN-A LAW.
        await client.expire(_voice_context_key(user_id), VOICE_CONTEXT_TTL_S)
        try:
            doc = json.loads(raw)
        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:
            _logger.warning(
                "voice.context.malformed",
                user_id=user_id,
                error=str(e),
            )
            return []
        turns = doc.get("turns") or []
        return turns if isinstance(turns, list) else []
    finally:
        await client.aclose()


async def _save_voice_context_redis(
    user_id: str, turns: list[dict[str, Any]]
) -> None:
    """Save voice:context:{user_id} to Redis with FIFO truncate + TTL.

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW: FIFO truncate at VOICE_CONTEXT_MAX_TURNS (5).
    TTL VOICE_CONTEXT_TTL_S (30min).
    """
    # FIFO truncate — keep most recent N turns.
    truncated = turns[-VOICE_CONTEXT_MAX_TURNS:]
    doc = {"turns": truncated, "updated_at": _now_iso()}
    client = aioredis.from_url(_redis_url(), decode_responses=True)
    try:
        await client.set(
            _voice_context_key(user_id),
            json.dumps(doc, ensure_ascii=False),
            ex=VOICE_CONTEXT_TTL_S,
        )
    finally:
        await client.aclose()


# ============================================================================
# Node helpers — emit_error_terminal, build_voice_history_text
# ============================================================================


async def _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
    rid: str,
    code: str,
    message_vi: str,
    details: Optional[dict[str, Any]] = None,
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Emit error SSE per D-S08-NN-11 LAW + set state.voice_action='__error__'
    so conditional edges short-circuit to final node.

    The 4 voice error codes (E_TRANSCRIBE_FAILED, E_INTENT_PARSE_FAILED,
    E_PERMISSION_DENIED, E_NO_SPEECH) are documented JSDoc-only in
    packages/shared-types/src/dto/error.dto.ts per S-07 E_VISION_BLUR
    precedent (NO new Zod enum).
    """
    payload = {
        "code": code,
        "message": message_vi,
        "request_id": rid,
    }
    if details:
        payload["details"] = details
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "error", payload)
    _logger.error(
        "voice.error_emitted",
        request_id=rid,
        code=code,
        message=message_vi,
    )
    # Set sentinel action so _route_by_voice_action falls through to final.
    return {"voice_action": "__error__"}


def _build_voice_history_text(turns: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> str:
    """Render voice_history as compact JSON for prompt injection."""
    if not turns:
        return "[]"
    # Strip large fields (matched_products full payload) to keep prompt small.
    compact = []
    for t in turns:
        compact.append({
            "user_utterance": t.get("user_utterance", ""),
            "action": t.get("action", ""),
            "parsed_items": t.get("parsed_items", []),
            "matched_products": [
                {"id": p.get("id"), "title": p.get("title")}
                for p in (t.get("matched_products") or [])[:5]
            ],
            "ai_summary_vi": t.get("ai_summary_vi", ""),
        })
    return json.dumps(compact, ensure_ascii=False)


def _build_cart_snapshot_text(cart: dict[str, Any]) -> str:
    """Render cart snapshot as compact JSON for prompt injection."""
    items = (cart or {}).get("items") or []
    compact = {
        "items": [
            {
                "product_id": it.get("product_id"),
                "title": it.get("title"),
                "qty": it.get("qty"),
            }
            for it in items
        ],
    }
    return json.dumps(compact, ensure_ascii=False)


# ============================================================================
# Node 1 — load_voice_context
# ============================================================================


async def _node_load_voice_context(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Load voice:context:{user_id} from Redis + cart.get from MCP.

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW cornerstone. Both reads in parallel via asyncio.gather.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    user_id = state.get("user_id") or "anon"

    with _tracer.start_as_current_span("voice.load_context") as span:
        span.set_attribute("voice.user_id", user_id)

        await publisher.publish_sse(
            rid,
            "status",
            {"phase": "load_context", "request_id": rid},
        )

        mcp = McpClient(_mcp_url(), timeout_s=10.0)
        try:
            voice_history, cart_data = await asyncio.gather(
                _load_voice_context_redis(user_id),
                mcp.call("cart.get", {"user_id": user_id}),
            )
        except McpError as e:
            _logger.warning(
                "voice.load_context.cart_get_failed",
                request_id=rid,
                user_id=user_id,
                error=str(e),
            )
            voice_history = await _load_voice_context_redis(user_id)
            cart_data = {"items": [], "totals": {"subtotal": 0}}

        span.set_attribute("voice.history_turns", len(voice_history))
        span.set_attribute("voice.cart_items",
                           len(((cart_data or {}).get("items") or [])))
        _logger.info(
            "voice.context_loaded",
            request_id=rid,
            user_id=user_id,
            history_turns=len(voice_history),
            cart_items=len(((cart_data or {}).get("items") or [])),
        )

    return {
        "voice_history": voice_history,
        "_cart_data": cart_data,
    }


# ============================================================================
# Node 2 — speech_transcribe
# ============================================================================


async def _node_speech_transcribe(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Call speech.transcribe MCP → emit voice_transcribed SSE.

    Per D-S08-NN-03 LAW (Gemini 2.5 Flash audio) + D-S08-NN-02 LAW
    (voice_transcribed event NEW per T01.G shared-types).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    audio_b64 = state.get("voice_audio_b64") or state.get("content") or ""

    if not audio_b64:
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_NO_SPEECH",
            "Không nhận được dữ liệu giọng nói. Bạn thử lại nhé.",
            {"retriable": True},
        )

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "phase_progress",
        {"phase": "transcribe", "request_id": rid},
    )

    mcp = McpClient(_mcp_url(), timeout_s=SPEECH_MCP_TIMEOUT_S)
    try:
        with _tracer.start_as_current_span("voice.transcribe") as span:
            result = await mcp.call(
                "speech.transcribe",
                {
                    "audio_b64": audio_b64,
                    "mime_type": "audio/webm",
                    "lang": "vi",
                },
            )
            span.set_attribute("voice.text_chars",
                               len((result or {}).get("text", "")))
    except McpError as e:
        # speech.py raises RuntimeError("E_TRANSCRIBE_FAILED: ...") /
        # RuntimeError("E_NO_SPEECH: ...") — MCP wraps as error.code -32603.
        # The error.data.detail string carries the E_* prefix.
        detail = (e.data or {}).get("detail", "") if isinstance(e.data, dict) else ""
        if "E_NO_SPEECH" in str(e) or "E_NO_SPEECH" in detail:
            return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
                publisher, rid, "E_NO_SPEECH",
                "Không nghe rõ, bạn nói lại nhé?",
                {"retriable": True},
            )
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_TRANSCRIBE_FAILED",
            "Em không nghe được, bạn thử lại nhé.",
            {"retriable": True, "detail": str(e)[:200]},
        )
    except Exception as e:  # noqa: BLE001 — defensive (httpx timeout, etc.)
        _logger.error("voice.transcribe.unexpected",
                      request_id=rid, error=str(e))
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_TRANSCRIBE_FAILED",
            "Em không nghe được, bạn thử lại nhé.",
            {"retriable": True, "detail": str(e)[:200]},
        )

    text = (result or {}).get("text", "").strip()
    confidence = result.get("confidence")  # MAY be None per R-S08-1
    duration_ms = int(result.get("duration_ms", 0))
    language = result.get("language", "vi")

    if not text:
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_NO_SPEECH",
            "Không nghe rõ, bạn nói lại nhé?",
            {"retriable": True},
        )

    # Emit NEW voice_transcribed event (T01.G per D-S08-NN-02 LAW).
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "voice_transcribed",
        {
            "type": "voice_transcribed",
            "text": text,
            "confidence": confidence,
            "duration_ms": duration_ms,
            "language": language,
        },
    )

    # Cosmetic partial_text per D-S08-NN-07 LAW — graph emits one partial
    # immediately; FE T02 simulates progressive typewriter via CSS.
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "partial_text",
        {"text": text, "delta": text, "request_id": rid},
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.transcribed",
        request_id=rid,
        text_chars=len(text),
        duration_ms=duration_ms,
        confidence=confidence,
    )

    return {
        "voice_text": text,
        "voice_confidence": confidence,
    }


# ============================================================================
# Node 3 — parse_voice_intent
# ============================================================================


async def _node_parse_voice_intent(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """LLM bulk-parse voice utterance → action enum + items list.

    Per D-S08-NN-04 LAW (LLMClient.generate_json reuse, 15s timeout) +
    D-S08-NN-B LAW (4 action enum: add/update_qty/remove/query) +
    D-S08-NN-A LAW (voice_history + cart_snapshot context injection).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]

    # Error short-circuit if upstream set sentinel.
    if state.get("voice_action") == "__error__":
        return {}

    voice_text = state.get("voice_text") or ""
    voice_history = state.get("voice_history") or []
    cart_data = state.get("_cart_data") or {}  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "phase_progress",
        {"phase": "parse", "request_id": rid},
    )

    template = load_prompt("parse_voice_intent")
    prompt = template.format(
        voice_history=_build_voice_history_text(voice_history),
        cart_snapshot=_build_cart_snapshot_text(cart_data),
        voice_text=voice_text,
    )

    llm = get_llm_client()
    try:
        with _tracer.start_as_current_span("voice.parse_intent") as span:
            parsed = await llm.generate_json(
                prompt=prompt,
                timeout_s=LLM_PARSE_TIMEOUT_S,
            )
            span.set_attribute("voice.action",
                               (parsed or {}).get("action", "unknown"))
            span.set_attribute("voice.items",
                               len((parsed or {}).get("items", [])))
    except LLMTimeout:
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_INTENT_PARSE_FAILED",
            "Em chưa hiểu rõ, bạn nói lại chậm hơn được không?",
            {"retriable": True, "reason": "llm_timeout"},
        )
    except Exception as e:  # noqa: BLE001
        _logger.error("voice.parse.unexpected",
                      request_id=rid, error=str(e))
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_INTENT_PARSE_FAILED",
            "Em chưa hiểu rõ, bạn nói lại chậm hơn được không?",
            {"retriable": True, "detail": str(e)[:200]},
        )

    action = (parsed or {}).get("action", "").strip()
    if action not in _VOICE_ACTIONS_ALL:
        _logger.warning(
            "voice.parse.unknown_action",
            request_id=rid,
            action=action,
            raw=parsed,
        )
        return await _emit_error_and_route_to_final(
            publisher, rid, "E_INTENT_PARSE_FAILED",
            "Em chưa hiểu rõ yêu cầu, bạn thử lại nhé.",
            {"retriable": True, "reason": "unknown_action", "action": action},
        )

    items_raw = (parsed or {}).get("items") or []
    if not isinstance(items_raw, list):
        items_raw = []
    items = items_raw[:MAX_VOICE_ITEMS]  # R-S08-6 soft cap

    ai_summary_vi = (parsed or {}).get("ai_summary_vi", "")

    # Emit understanding SSE (reuse S-04 event per D-S08-NN-02 LAW).
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "understanding",
        {
            "text": ai_summary_vi or voice_text,
            "request_id": rid,
        },
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.parsed",
        request_id=rid,
        action=action,
        item_count=len(items),
        confidence=(parsed or {}).get("confidence"),
    )

    return {
        "voice_action": action,
        "voice_parsed_items": items,
    }


# ============================================================================
# Node 4a — resolve_items (action=add|update_qty)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_resolve_items(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Parallel Vespa hybrid_search per voice item.

    Per D-S08-NN-05 LAW (asyncio.gather parallel Vespa per item).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    items = state.get("voice_parsed_items") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    voice_history = state.get("voice_history") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "phase_progress",
        {"phase": "resolve", "request_id": rid},
    )

    if not items:
        return {"voice_matched_products": []}

    mcp = McpClient(_mcp_url(), timeout_s=20.0)

    async def _resolve_one(idx: int, item: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:
        # Ordinal reference path — re-use prior turn matched_products per
        # D-S08-NN-A LAW (no fresh Vespa search).
        ordinal = item.get("ordinal_ref")
        if isinstance(ordinal, int) and voice_history:
            last_turn = voice_history[-1]
            prior = (last_turn.get("matched_products") or [])
            if 1 <= ordinal <= len(prior):
                picked = prior[ordinal - 1]
                return {
                    "item_idx": idx,
                    "query": item.get("query") or "[ordinal]",
                    "qty": int(item.get("qty", 1)),
                    "matched_product": picked,
                    "candidates": [picked],
                    "match_score": 1.0,
                    "resolution": "ordinal",
                }
        # Fresh Vespa search path.
        query = (item.get("query") or "").strip()
        if not query:
            return {
                "item_idx": idx,
                "query": "",
                "qty": int(item.get("qty", 0)),
                "matched_product": None,
                "candidates": [],
                "match_score": 0.0,
                "resolution": "empty_query",
            }
        try:
            result = await mcp.call(
                "vespa.hybrid_search",
                {"query": query, "limit": VESPA_RESOLVE_LIMIT},
            )
        except McpError as e:
            _logger.warning(
                "voice.resolve.vespa_error",
                request_id=rid,
                query=query,
                error=str(e),
            )
            return {
                "item_idx": idx,
                "query": query,
                "qty": int(item.get("qty", 0)),
                "matched_product": None,
                "candidates": [],
                "match_score": 0.0,
                "resolution": "vespa_error",
            }
        hits = (result or {}).get("items") or (result or {}).get("hits") or []
        if not hits:
            return {
                "item_idx": idx,
                "query": query,
                "qty": int(item.get("qty", 0)),
                "matched_product": None,
                "candidates": [],
                "match_score": 0.0,
                "resolution": "no_match",
            }
        top = hits[0]
        # C-S08-Q FIX: Vespa hybrid_search returns "match_score" (not
        # "score"/"relevance"). Prior code read missing keys => 0.0 =>
        # everything routed to no_match. Read match_score first.
        score = float(
            top.get("match_score", top.get("score", top.get("relevance", 0.0)))
            or 0.0
        )
        return {
            "item_idx": idx,
            "query": query,
            "qty": int(item.get("qty", 0)),
            "unit": item.get("unit"),
            "matched_product": top,
            "candidates": hits[:5],
            "match_score": score,
            "resolution": "vespa",
        }

    matched = await asyncio.gather(*[
        _resolve_one(i, it) for i, it in enumerate(items)
    ])

    _logger.info(
        "voice.resolved",
        request_id=rid,
        item_count=len(items),
        matched_count=sum(1 for m in matched if m.get("matched_product")),
    )

    return {"voice_matched_products": list(matched)}


# ============================================================================
# Node 4b — voice_cart_remove (action=remove)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_voice_cart_remove(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Resolve product_id from cart snapshot by voice match → cart.update_qty(qty=0).

    Per D-S08-NN-06 LAW (Redis cart JSON snapshot reuse, no HASH).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    user_id = state.get("user_id") or "anon"
    items = state.get("voice_parsed_items") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    cart_data = state.get("_cart_data") or {}  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    cart_items = (cart_data.get("items") or []) if isinstance(cart_data, dict) else []

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "phase_progress",
        {"phase": "cart_remove", "request_id": rid},
    )

    mcp = McpClient(_mcp_url(), timeout_s=10.0)
    removed_count = 0
    final_cart = cart_data

    for vit in items:
        query = (vit.get("query") or "").lower().strip()
        if not query:
            continue
        # Naive substring match by title — sufficient for VN voice remove
        # use case (user typically says brand or product name).
        match = next(
            (
                ci for ci in cart_items
                if query in (ci.get("title") or "").lower()
            ),
            None,
        )
        if not match:
            _logger.info(
                "voice.remove.no_match_in_cart",
                request_id=rid,
                query=query,
            )
            continue
        product_id = match.get("product_id")
        if not product_id:
            continue
        try:
            final_cart = await mcp.call(
                "cart.update_qty",
                {"user_id": user_id, "product_id": product_id, "qty": 0},
            )
            removed_count += 1
        except McpError as e:
            _logger.warning(
                "voice.remove.mcp_error",
                request_id=rid,
                product_id=product_id,
                error=str(e),
            )

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "cart_updated",
        {
            "request_id": rid,
            "cart": final_cart,
            "removed_count": removed_count,
        },
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.removed",
        request_id=rid,
        removed_count=removed_count,
    )

    return {"_cart_data": final_cart}


# ============================================================================
# Node 4c — voice_recall (action=query)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_voice_recall(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Recall from voice_history with NO Vespa, NO cart mutation.

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW state-recall path. ai_summary_vi already populated by
    Node 3 parse_voice_intent per parse_voice_intent.txt instruction 4.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    # parse_voice_intent already emitted understanding SSE in Node 3.
    # No additional work here — just route to save_voice_context.
    _logger.info("voice.recall_done", request_id=rid)
    return {}


# ============================================================================
# Node 5 — voice_no_match_alts (all_no_match path)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_voice_no_match_alts(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Suggest alternatives for queries with no high-confidence match.

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW state-F path + S-05 D-S05-04 LAW pattern reuse
    (vespa.hybrid_search similarity + LLM 1-line reason).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    matched = state.get("voice_matched_products") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "phase_progress",
        {"phase": "no_match_alts", "request_id": rid},
    )

    # Gather alternatives from candidates already fetched in resolve_items.
    alts = []
    llm = get_llm_client()
    template = load_prompt("voice_no_match_reason")

    for m in matched:
        if m.get("matched_product"):
            continue  # has a match; not in no-match path for this item
        candidates = m.get("candidates") or []
        if not candidates:
            continue
        alt = candidates[0]
        query = m.get("query") or ""
        # 1-line VN reason per S-05 D-S05-04 LAW precedent.
        prompt = template.format(
            voice_query=query,
            alt_product_title=alt.get("title", ""),
            alt_brand=alt.get("brand", ""),
            alt_category=alt.get("category", ""),
            similarity_pct=int(float(alt.get("score", 0.0)) * 100),
        )
        try:
            reason_doc = await llm.generate_json(
                prompt=prompt, timeout_s=8.0,
            )
            reason = (reason_doc or {}).get("reason", "")
        except LLMTimeout:
            reason = f"Cùng nhóm sản phẩm, có thể thay thế."
        except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001
            reason = f"Cùng nhóm sản phẩm, có thể thay thế."

        alts.append({
            "item_idx": m.get("item_idx"),
            "original_query": query,
            "alternative": alt,
            "reason": reason,
        })

    # Reuse stock_issue_summary event as terminal no-match summary
    # (D-S08-NN-02 LAW SSE event reuse — no new event type).
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "stock_issue_summary",
        {
            "request_id": rid,
            "reason": "voice_no_match",
            "alternatives": alts,
        },
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.no_match_alts_emitted",
        request_id=rid,
        alt_count=len(alts),
    )

    return {}


# ============================================================================
# Node 6 — bulk_cart_commit (some_matched ambiguous interrupt OR all_matched)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_route_resolution(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Apply thresholds + decide: all_matched / some_ambiguous / all_no_match.

    On some_ambiguous: emit status awaiting_user_input + interrupt({
        awaiting: 'clarify_pick'}). FE state-D chip-row resume per MAR-1 Q1
    LOCKED.

    Per D-S08-NN-10 LAW (env-tunable thresholds 0.85 high / 0.6 low) +
    D-S08-NN-01 LAW (Pattern A interrupt+resume reuse).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    matched = state.get("voice_matched_products") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    if not matched:
        return {"voice_clarify_pending": False}
    # C-S08-Q: classify each item via top1 floor + top2/top1 ratio.
    classes = [_voice_match_class(m) for m in matched]
    ambiguous = [m for m, c in zip(matched, classes) if c == "ambiguous"]
    # No ambiguous items → no clarify interrupt (downstream conditional
    # routes to commit if any match, else no_match_alts).
    if not ambiguous:
        return {"voice_clarify_pending": False}

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "status",
        {"phase": "awaiting_user_input", "request_id": rid,
         "reason": "voice_clarify"},
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.interrupt_clarify",
        request_id=rid,
        ambiguous_count=len(ambiguous),
    )
    # C-S08-R: push chip-row candidate data to FE over SSE BEFORE the
    # interrupt() (whose payload never reaches FE — main.py discards
    # astream chunks). FE state-D renders .opt-chip from this event.
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "voice_clarify_options",
        {
            "request_id": rid,
            "ambiguous_items": [
                {"item_idx": m.get("item_idx"),
                 "query": m.get("query"),
                 "qty": m.get("qty"),
                 "candidates": [
                     _voice_candidate_chip(c)
                     for c in (m.get("candidates") or [])[:3]
                 ]}
                for m in ambiguous
            ],
        },
    )

    # Pattern A interrupt — graph pauses, RedisSaver persists.
    resume = interrupt({
        "awaiting": "clarify_pick",
        "ambiguous_items": [
            {"item_idx": m.get("item_idx"),
             "query": m.get("query"),
             "qty": m.get("qty"),
             "candidates": [
                 _voice_candidate_chip(c)
                 for c in (m.get("candidates") or [])[:3]
             ]}
            for m in ambiguous
        ],
    })

    choice = (resume or {}).get("choice")
    value = (resume or {}).get("value") or {}
    _logger.info(
        "voice.resumed",
        request_id=rid,
        node="route_resolution",
        choice=choice,
        product_id=value.get("product_id"),
    )

    if choice != "clarify_pick":
        # Unexpected choice — log + proceed anyway with current matches.
        return {"voice_clarify_pending": False}

    # Apply picked product_id to first ambiguous item (FE picks one at a
    # time per mockup state-D chip-row UI).
    picked_id = value.get("product_id")
    if picked_id and ambiguous:
        first_amb = ambiguous[0]
        item_idx = first_amb.get("item_idx")
        # Find picked candidate to set as matched_product.
        candidates = first_amb.get("candidates") or []
        picked_product = next(
            (c for c in candidates if c.get("id") == picked_id),
            {"id": picked_id, "title": "(picked)"},
        )
        # Mutate the matched_products list in place.
        for m in matched:
            if m.get("item_idx") == item_idx:
                m["matched_product"] = picked_product
                m["match_score"] = 1.0
                m["resolution"] = "clarify_pick"
                break

    return {
        "voice_matched_products": matched,
        "voice_clarify_pending": False,
    }


async def _node_bulk_cart_commit(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Loop cart.update_qty per matched item → emit cart_updated SSE.

    Per D-S08-NN-08 LAW (Redis pipeline-style loop). MCP cart.update_qty is
    atomic per-call (cart.py uses Redis lock per user_id); we sequence calls
    to maintain consistent intermediate states for each item.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    user_id = state.get("user_id") or "anon"
    matched = state.get("voice_matched_products") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    voice_action = state.get("voice_action") or "add"

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "phase_progress",
        {"phase": "cart_commit", "request_id": rid},
    )

    mcp = McpClient(_mcp_url(), timeout_s=15.0)
    committed_count = 0
    final_cart: dict[str, Any] = state.get("_cart_data") or {}  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]

    for m in matched:
        product = m.get("matched_product")
        if not product:
            continue
        product_id = product.get("id")
        qty = int(m.get("qty", 1))
        if not product_id or qty < 0:
            continue
        # For update_qty action: add the parsed qty to existing cart qty.
        if voice_action == "update_qty":
            existing = next(
                (it for it in ((final_cart.get("items") or [])
                               if isinstance(final_cart, dict) else [])
                 if it.get("product_id") == product_id),
                None,
            )
            if existing:
                qty = int(existing.get("qty", 0)) + qty

        snapshot = {
            "title": product.get("title"),
            "image_url": product.get("image_url"),
            "category": product.get("category"),
            "brand": product.get("brand"),
        }
        try:
            final_cart = await mcp.call(
                "cart.update_qty",
                {
                    "user_id": user_id,
                    "product_id": product_id,
                    "qty": qty,
                    "snapshot": snapshot,
                },
            )
            committed_count += 1
        except McpError as e:
            _logger.warning(
                "voice.commit.mcp_error",
                request_id=rid,
                product_id=product_id,
                error=str(e),
            )

    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "cart_updated",
        {
            "request_id": rid,
            "cart": final_cart,
            "committed_count": committed_count,
            "action": voice_action,
        },
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.committed",
        request_id=rid,
        committed_count=committed_count,
        action=voice_action,
    )

    return {"_cart_data": final_cart}


# ============================================================================
# Node 7 — co_purchase_lookup (S-04 reuse per D-S08-NN-05 LAW)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_co_purchase_lookup(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """analytics.co_purchased reuse per D-S08-NN-05 LAW (S-04 D-S04-NN reuse).

    Light wrapper — picks first committed product as anchor, calls analytics
    MCP, emits co_purchase_hint SSE if match found.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    matched = state.get("voice_matched_products") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]

    # Pick first successfully matched product as anchor.
    anchor = next(
        (m.get("matched_product") for m in matched if m.get("matched_product")),
        None,
    )
    if not anchor:
        return {}

    anchor_id = anchor.get("id")
    anchor_category = anchor.get("category")
    if not anchor_category:
        return {}

    mcp = McpClient(_mcp_url(), timeout_s=10.0)
    try:
        result = await mcp.call(
            "analytics.co_purchased",
            {"anchor_category": anchor_category, "limit": 1},
        )
    except McpError as e:
        _logger.info(
            "voice.copurchase.mcp_skip",
            request_id=rid,
            error=str(e),
        )
        return {}

    entries = (result or {}).get("entries") or []
    if not entries:
        return {}

    top = entries[0]
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "co_purchase_hint",
        {
            "anchor_product_id": anchor_id,
            "anchor_category": anchor_category,
            "suggested_category": top.get("suggested_category"),
            "suggested_product_id": top.get("suggested_product_id"),
            "rate_pct": int(top.get("rate_pct", 0)),
            "reason": top.get("reason", ""),
        },
    )

    _logger.info(
        "voice.copurchase_emitted",
        request_id=rid,
        anchor_id=anchor_id,
    )

    return {}


# ============================================================================
# Node 8 — save_voice_context (D-S08-NN-A LAW persistence)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_save_voice_context(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Save this turn to voice:context:{user_id} with FIFO 5 + TTL 30min.

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW cornerstone. NOTE: voice:context PERSISTS across
    Strategy β saver.adelete_thread(rid) call in _node_final because they
    are SEPARATE Redis keys per cornerstone architectural decision.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    user_id = state.get("user_id") or "anon"

    # Build this turn record.
    matched = state.get("voice_matched_products") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    parsed_items = state.get("voice_parsed_items") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    voice_action = state.get("voice_action") or ""

    # Skip persisting if action was __error__ (no useful turn data).
    if voice_action == "__error__":
        return {}

    this_turn = {
        "request_id": rid,
        "user_utterance": state.get("voice_text", ""),
        "action": voice_action,
        "parsed_items": parsed_items,
        "matched_products": [
            m.get("matched_product")
            for m in matched
            if m.get("matched_product")
        ],
        "ai_summary_vi": "",  # reserved; can be populated by parse node if added
        "ts": _now_iso(),
    }

    existing = state.get("voice_history") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    new_history = list(existing) + [this_turn]

    try:
        await _save_voice_context_redis(user_id, new_history)
        _logger.info(
            "voice.context_saved",
            request_id=rid,
            user_id=user_id,
            total_turns=len(new_history[-VOICE_CONTEXT_MAX_TURNS:]),
        )
    except Exception as e:  # noqa: BLE001
        _logger.warning(
            "voice.context_save_failed",
            request_id=rid,
            user_id=user_id,
            error=str(e),
        )

    return {}


# ============================================================================
# Node 9 — final (Strategy β fast-path cleanup)
# ============================================================================


async def _node_final(
    state: IcpState, publisher: RedisPublisher, saver: Any
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Terminal node — emit final SSE + Strategy β fast-path RedisSaver cleanup.

    Mirrors searching_by_text.py + cart_by_text.py:_node_final pattern.
    voice:context:{user_id} PERSISTS in separate Redis key per
    D-S08-NN-A LAW cornerstone (cleanup only touches intent:checkpoint:{rid}).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    voice_action = state.get("voice_action", "")
    await publisher.publish_sse(
        rid,
        "final",
        {
            "request_id": rid,
            "modality": "voice",
            "voice_action": voice_action,
        },
    )
    try:
        await saver.adelete_thread(rid)
        _logger.info("intent.checkpoint_cleaned", request_id=rid)
    except Exception as e:  # noqa: BLE001
        _logger.warning(
            "intent.checkpoint_cleanup_failed",
            request_id=rid,
            error=str(e),
        )
    return {}


# ============================================================================
# Conditional edge functions
# ============================================================================


def _route_by_voice_action(state: IcpState) -> str:
    """Conditional edge after parse_voice_intent → dispatch by action enum.

    Per D-S08-NN-B LAW. '__error__' sentinel short-circuits to final.
    """
    action = state.get("voice_action", "")
    if action == "__error__":
        return "final"
    if action == "remove":
        return "voice_cart_remove"
    if action == "query":
        return "voice_recall"
    # add / update_qty → resolve_items
    if action in ("add", "update_qty"):
        return "resolve_items"
    _logger.warning("voice.unknown_action_route",
                    action=action)
    return "final"


def _route_after_resolution(state: IcpState) -> str:
    """Conditional edge after resolve_items + route_resolution.

    Decides: bulk_cart_commit (all matched after possible clarify_pick) OR
    voice_no_match_alts (all low score).
    """
    matched = state.get("voice_matched_products") or []  # type: ignore[typeddict-item]
    if not matched:
        return "voice_no_match_alts"
    # C-S08-Q: if at least one item is a confident match, commit (ambiguous
    # items were handled by clarify interrupt in route_resolution upstream).
    match_count = sum(1 for m in matched if _voice_match_class(m) == "match")
    if match_count > 0:
        return "bulk_cart_commit"
    return "voice_no_match_alts"


# ============================================================================
# Graph builder — compile_buying_by_voices_graph(saver, publisher)
# ============================================================================


def compile_buying_by_voices_graph(
    saver: AsyncRedisSaver, publisher: RedisPublisher
) -> Any:
    """Compile the buying_by_voices graph with pre-initialized AsyncRedisSaver
    + RedisPublisher.

    Caller (main.py) owns saver + publisher lifecycle per Phiên Sx04-7 fix
    LAW. saver MUST have been entered as `async with
    AsyncRedisSaver.from_conn_string(...)` AND `await saver.asetup()` called
    BEFORE this function is invoked.

    Per D-S04-13 LAW Pattern A:
        - AsyncRedisSaver as checkpointer
        - StateGraph.compile(checkpointer=saver)
        - thread_id passed via config in main.py invocation

    Per D-S04-13 LAW Strategy β:
        - ttl={'default_ttl': 30, 'refresh_on_read': True}  (configured by caller)
        - adelete_thread(rid) called explicitly at final node

    Per D-S08-NN-A LAW cornerstone (voice memory hybrid):
        - voice:context:{user_id} is a SEPARATE Redis key (NOT touched by
          saver.adelete_thread) with its own TTL 30min refresh-on-read,
          FIFO 5 turns persistence.

    Args:
        saver:     AsyncRedisSaver already entered + asetup() called.
        publisher: RedisPublisher (lazy-init OK; no setup required).

    Returns:
        Compiled LangGraph ready for `.astream(initial_state, config)`.
    """
    # Wrap each node closure binding publisher (+ saver for final cleanup).
    async def n_load_voice_context(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_load_voice_context(s, publisher)

    async def n_speech_transcribe(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_speech_transcribe(s, publisher)

    async def n_parse_voice_intent(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_parse_voice_intent(s, publisher)

    async def n_resolve_items(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_resolve_items(s, publisher)

    async def n_voice_cart_remove(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_voice_cart_remove(s, publisher)

    async def n_voice_recall(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_voice_recall(s, publisher)

    async def n_route_resolution(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_route_resolution(s, publisher)

    async def n_voice_no_match_alts(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_voice_no_match_alts(s, publisher)

    async def n_bulk_cart_commit(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_bulk_cart_commit(s, publisher)

    async def n_co_purchase_lookup(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_co_purchase_lookup(s, publisher)

    async def n_save_voice_context(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_save_voice_context(s, publisher)

    async def n_final(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_final(s, publisher, saver)

    g = StateGraph(IcpState)
    g.add_node("load_voice_context", n_load_voice_context)
    g.add_node("speech_transcribe", n_speech_transcribe)
    g.add_node("parse_voice_intent", n_parse_voice_intent)
    g.add_node("resolve_items", n_resolve_items)
    g.add_node("voice_cart_remove", n_voice_cart_remove)
    g.add_node("voice_recall", n_voice_recall)
    g.add_node("route_resolution", n_route_resolution)
    g.add_node("voice_no_match_alts", n_voice_no_match_alts)
    g.add_node("bulk_cart_commit", n_bulk_cart_commit)
    g.add_node("co_purchase_lookup", n_co_purchase_lookup)
    g.add_node("save_voice_context", n_save_voice_context)
    g.add_node("final", n_final)

    # Linear early stages
    g.add_edge(START, "load_voice_context")
    g.add_edge("load_voice_context", "speech_transcribe")
    g.add_edge("speech_transcribe", "parse_voice_intent")

    # Conditional dispatch by voice_action (D-S08-NN-B LAW)
    g.add_conditional_edges(
        "parse_voice_intent",
        _route_by_voice_action,
        {
            "resolve_items": "resolve_items",
            "voice_cart_remove": "voice_cart_remove",
            "voice_recall": "voice_recall",
            "final": "final",
        },
    )

    # resolve_items → route_resolution (interrupt handling) → conditional
    g.add_edge("resolve_items", "route_resolution")
    g.add_conditional_edges(
        "route_resolution",
        _route_after_resolution,
        {
            "bulk_cart_commit": "bulk_cart_commit",
            "voice_no_match_alts": "voice_no_match_alts",
        },
    )

    # Linear tail for committing actions
    g.add_edge("bulk_cart_commit", "co_purchase_lookup")
    g.add_edge("co_purchase_lookup", "save_voice_context")

    # Remove + recall paths skip co_purchase / commit, go straight to save
    g.add_edge("voice_cart_remove", "save_voice_context")
    g.add_edge("voice_recall", "save_voice_context")
    g.add_edge("voice_no_match_alts", "save_voice_context")

    g.add_edge("save_voice_context", "final")
    g.add_edge("final", END)

    compiled = g.compile(checkpointer=saver)
    return compiled
